                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-751-offence-1 t18390204-cd-196"></join>25th of January</rs>, 15 yards of ribbon, value 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390204-name-1250" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1250" type="surname" value="BIRD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1250" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-751-offence-1 t18390204-name-1250"></join>Thomas Bird</persName> and another.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1251" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1251" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1251" type="given" value="JOSEPH JEFFERSON"></interp>JOSEPH JEFFERSON EDWARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Thomas Bird and an<lb></lb>other, haberdashers, in Commercial-road. On the 25th of January, between two and three o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoners came in together, and asked to look at some bonnet-ribbon—I showed them the drawer of rib<lb></lb>bons—Elizabeth proposed to buy them—while she was looking at them, I saw Eliza concealing something under her cloak—they shortly after said we had no ribbon to suit them, and went out—I immediately missed the ribbon produced—they had but just got outside the door—I brought them back, and said they had taken a piece of green satin ribbon—Eliza said, "Search me," and began pulling off her cloak, and in the mean time this piece of ribbon fell—she said it fell from the counter, but I saw it fall from her person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where were you standing when you brought them into the shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> By the side of them—I have al<lb></lb>ways been confident that I saw the ribbon fall from under Eliza's cloak.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1252" type="witnessName">
